## ⚡ Performance Bottlenecks — Where It's Laggy

### 🔴 1. Background Worker Thread (FIXED in last session)
Was using module-level mutable globals — duplicate threads spawned on reruns.
✅ **Now fixed** using `st.cache_resource` singleton.

### 🟠 2. Loading 20MB+ Demo CSV on Every Session
[manufacturing_6G_dataset.csv](file:///c:/Users/Himanshu/OneDrive/Desktop/Hackthone/manufacturing_6G_dataset.csv) is loaded fresh whenever the feature store cache misses.
On a slow PC this takes 3–8 seconds. This is the main perceived lag.
**Fix:** Pre-build and commit the compressed feature store cache (`artifacts/feature_store/`).

### 🟠 3. Pareto Front is O(n²) for Large Datasets
At 50,000+ rows, 50,000 iterations × matrix operations gets slow.
**Fix:** Already vectorized — but add an early row-cap (`MAX_PARETO_ROWS = 10000`) with random sampling for very large datasets.

### 🟡 4. `app.py` is 1,380+ Lines — Full Re-render on Every Widget Click
Streamlit re-runs the entire file top-to-bottom on every button press.
**Fix:** Split into pages: `pages/01_Dashboard.py`, `pages/02_Optimizer.py` etc. (Streamlit multi-page).

### 🟡 5. `learning.py` Surrogate Model Re-trains Every Session
The `GradientBoostingRegressor` we added trains fresh every time the app loads.
**Fix:** Persist the trained model in `artifacts/` and reload if features haven't changed.

